\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/cmf.defining_polynomial}{Defining polynomial}}
\begin{definition*}\label{cmf.defining_polynomial}
\uses{cmf.coefficient_field,nf}
The \hyperref[cmf.coefficient_field]{coefficient field of a modular form} is a \hyperref[nf]{number field}. A \textbf{defining polynomial} for this number field is explicitly recorded, because some of the data associated to the modular form will be expressed in terms of roots of this polynomial.
\end{definition*}


